data.meta_description: English Monarch. The eldest son of Henry III and Eleanor of Provence, he was known as Longshanks and Hammer of the Scots. He ascended the throne upon the death of Henry III in 1272, but was not formally crowned until August 19, 1274. He married Eleanor of Castile at Burgos, Spain, on October 18, 1254.
